Staff Job Openings       Faculty Job Openings   Full-Time Lecturer Positions  Jane Addams College of Social Work invites applications for the position of lecturer from candidates with a commitment to social work’s role in the promotion of social, racial, and economic justice for urban communities. Candidates for these non-tenure track positions must possess a master’s degree in social work and at least two years of post-MSW practice experience. Candidates with interest in online and blended education as well as those with experience in substance use treatment and the CADC credential are strongly encouraged to apply.  These positions are full-time, 9-month faculty appointments in the MSW Program and include teaching a combination of social work courses which could include generalist practice, mental health practice, school social work, and/or human behavior in the social environment. In addition to teaching, lecturers participate in departmental meetings, provide academic advising, and maintain communication with students, faculty and the University as required.  Appointments will start August 16, 2020.  To apply please submit a letter of application, curriculum vitae, and the name and address of three references to Christopher Mitchell, Faculty Search Committee Chairperson. All applications must be submitted online through the following link: https://jobs.uic.edu/job-board/job-details?jobID=131605 . Completed applications should be received by June 1, 2020 for fullest consideration.  The University of Illinois at Chicago is an Equal Opportunity, Affirmative Action employer. Minorities, women, veterans and individuals with disabilities are encouraged to apply.  The University of Illinois may conduct background checks on all job candidates upon acceptance of a contingent offer. Background checks will be performed in compliance with the Fair Credit Reporting Act.       Staff Job Openings   No job openings at this time.          About    Back to main content           O